main event: Multiple UFO sightings reported in Portsmouth, VA, on 6/23/52 and 12/6/57, with one object observed for 10-15 minutes and seen flying in different directions.
interesting points: The sightings included a spinning disk with cones and flakes observed by a civilian and military aircraft personnel.
Unusual heavy air traffic was reported in the area during one of the sightings, including low-flying civilian transport and high-flying military aircraft.
One of the observers admitted to previously looking at a spinning disk as part of an eye examination, adding an intriguing detail to the report.
The document contains codes and classifications such as 'AFFIR DISK' and 'CLASSIFIED ACC OPS 3 5542', indicating the level of importance and secrecy surrounding the sightings.
The report concludes with 'CE' and 'INCONCLUSIVE', suggesting that the nature of the sightings could not be definitively determined.
sighted object: spinning disk with cones and flakes
